//*Supermarket Discount Billing (Using for Loop)*
*A supermarket applies the following discount rules on each item:*
1.If the item price is greater than or equal to 500, apply 20% discount.
2.If the item price is between 200 and 499, apply 10% discount.
3.If the item price is less than 200, no discount is applied.
Your task is to calculate the final total bill after discounts using a for loop.
*Test Case 01 :*
Input:
Items = [600, 250, 150, 800]
Output:
Total Bill after discount = 1495
*Test Case 02 :*
Input :
Items = [100, 300, 550]
Output :
Total Bill after discount = 810

import java.util.Scanner;

public class SupermarketDiscountBilling {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Input number of items
        System.out.print("Enter number of items: ");
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        int[] items = new int[n];
        double totalBill = 0;

        // Input item prices
        System.out.println("Enter price of each item:");
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            items[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }

        // Calculate total bill after discount
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            double price = items[i];
            double finalPrice;

            if (price >= 500) {
                finalPrice = price - (price * 0.20); // 20% discount
            } else if (price >= 200) {
                finalPrice = price - (price * 0.10); // 10% discount
            } else {
                finalPrice = price; // No discount
            }

            totalBill += finalPrice;
        }

        // Output
        System.out.println("Total Bill after discount = " + (int) totalBill);

        sc.close();
    }
}
